<p id="fs-idp221135936">Determine the empirical formulas for the following compounds:</p>
<p id="fs-idp205182832">(a) caffeine, C<sub>8</sub>H<sub>10</sub>N<sub>4</sub>O<sub>2</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm81581680">(b) fructose, C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp37339328">(c) hydrogen peroxide, H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp60210848">(d) glucose, C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>12</sub>O<sub>6</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm158214256">(e) ascorbic acid (vitamin C), C<sub>6</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>6</sub></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm69172608">
<p id="fs-idm44452624">(a) C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N<sub>2</sub>O; (b) C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub>; (c) HO; (d) CH<sub>2</sub>O; (e) C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O<sub>3</sub></p>
</div>
</div>
