<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp109292528">
<p id="fs-idp45758256">Use the <a href="http://openstaxcollege.org/l/16molbuilding">Build a Molecule simulation</a> to repeat <a href="#fs-idm75792016" class="autogenerated-content">[link]</a>, but build a molecule with three carbons, seven hydrogens, and one chlorine.</p>
<p id="fs-idm81559456">(a) Draw the structural formula of this molecule and state its name.</p>
<p id="fs-idm192066352">(b) Can you arrange these atoms to make a different molecule? If so, draw its structural formula and state its name.</p>
<p id="fs-idm112148224">(c) How are the molecules drawn in (a) and (b) the same? How do they differ? What are they called (the type of relationship between these molecules, not their names)?</p>
